description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit two individuals to join our busy department as a switchboard and portering/transport helpdesk operator based at Castle Hill Hospital as a casual worker on an as and when required basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role we are looking for experienced operators who can cover a 24 hour service that runs 7 days a week. This job would suit candidates who enjoy the flexibility of working unsocial hours and be flexible to cover at short notice. The shifts include days, lates, nights, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will act as a first point of contact for Hull University Teaching Hospitals providing an effective, efficient and professional service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must possess a high level of customer service and communication skills, work as a team and be fully conversant in computer and keyboard skills. The ability to multi-task, delegate and co-ordinate is required as part of the operator role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to deal with emergency calls and a variety of alarms and alerts in a calm and efficient manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous NHS experience in a similar role would be advantageous&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**Salary reflects year 3 of 3 years NHS pay deal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details and to arrange an informal visit please contact Mrs Sharon Dawson or Mrs Adele Latus, Communications Centre Managers on 624010&lt;/p&gt;
